Description: Resampling and related methods for data under dependence 
  and uneven groups. Methods of resampling, cross-validation, and forecasting 
  confidence intervals purify the data by with potential dependence or stratified 
  sampling resulting in improved conclusions under a variety of scenarios. 
  Functions are robust and flexible permitting direct use or seamless integration 
  into the custom analyses. Discussions on bootstrapping, permutation, and 
  cross-validation can be found in works such as Efron, B., & Tibshirani, R. 
  (1993) <doi:10.1201/9780429246593> and Anthony C., & Hinkley, D. V. (1997) 
  <doi:10.2307/1271471>. Sampling methods, with comments on stratification, are 
  found in Thompson, S. K. (2012) <doi:10.1002/9781118162934>. Examples which use 
  this package include Tetui et al. (2022) <doi:10.1080/21645515.2022.2089500> 
  and Alexander, K. L., Hall, K., & Chen, Y. M. (2024) <doi:10.29173/jchla29798>.
